{{see|sinn}}
==German==

===Etymology===
Old High German ''[[sin]]''

===Noun===
'''Sinn''' {{m}}

# [[sense]], [[meaning]]
# [[point]], [[idea]], [[tenor]]
# [[mind]], [[consciousness]]
# [[feeling]]
# (''med'') [[sense]], [[sensus]], [[aesthesia]] (''Brit'')/[[esthesia]] (''Am'')

===Related terms===
*[[Sensus]]
*[[sinnen]]
*[[sinnig]]
*[[sinlich]]
*[[sinnlos]]
*[[sinnvoll]]

===Compounds===
*[[Sinngebung]]
*[[Sinnesnerv]]
*[[Sinnestäuschung]]
*[[Sinneswahrnehmung]]

===Usage===
* ''Sinn haben'', ''Sinn ergeben'' - to make sense
* ''im Sinn haben'' - to have in mind
* ''in den Sinn kommen'' - to cross so.'s mind
* ''in jedem Sinn'' - in every sense
* ''der Sinn und Zweck'' - the whole purpose
* ''lange Rede kurzer Sinn'' - to cut a long story short
* ''ohne Sinn und Verstand'' - nonsensically
* ''Aus den Augen, aus dem Sinn'' - out of sight, out of mind

